│ means for some lanes the divisor may be 0, and dividing by 0 is               │
│ poison/undefined. Threading udiv over that select can cause the simplifier to │
│ attempt to simplify each arm (udiv by -1 and udiv by 0/1) and then            │
│ incorrectly conclude a uniform result (e.g., zeros), ignoring the undefined   │
│ path or collapsing poison to zero.                                            │
│                                                                               │
