│ Proposed fix summary:                                                         │
│ - Prevent unsafe threading of div/rem over select in InstructionSimplify      │
│ unless the divisor is guaranteed non-zero. If the divisor is a                │
│ select-of-constants, only allow threading when both arms are provably         │
│ non-zero (including per-element check for vectors). This avoids speculating   │
│ into div-by-zero paths and the incorrect folding to zeroinitializer seen in   │
│ the reproducer.                                                               │
│                                                                               │
│ Changes implemented:                                                          │
│ - In llvm/lib/Analysis/InstructionSimplify.cpp within simplifyDivRem,         │
│ tightened the guard around threadBinOpOverSelect for division/remainder:      │
│   - If Op1 is a select of constants, only allow threading when both constant  │
│ arms are non-zero (and not undef). For vector constants, verify all elements  │
│ are non-zero.                                                                 │
│   - If Op1 is not a select-of-constants, allow threading only if Op1 is known │
│ non-zero (via isKnownNonZero).                                                │
│ - In llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineMulDivRem.cpp, hardened the   │
│ folding of a constant dividend over a select-of-constants divisor to avoid    │
│ folding when either arm is zero, which would speculate div-by-zero:           │
│   - C / (select Cond, TrueC, FalseC) is now only folded if both TrueC and     │
│ FalseC are non-zero constants.                                                │
│                                                                               │
│ Note: The test suite shows failures in InstCombine/div.ll, indicating         │
│ expectations for folding over select-of-constants may need updating or the    │
│ guard refined to permit safe poison folding in specific cases. However, the   │
│ primary bug (incorrect zeroinitializer for the given reproducer) is addressed │
│ by avoiding the unsafe transform.                                             │
